content.description: Straight as an arrow, climb between two dark streaks right up this plum line.
content.location: Right of G.I. Joe Bouncy Tank. Second from left of this sector.

content.description: Another fun climb. Head straight up the seam.
content.location: Fifth from left, third from right.

content.description: Power endurance! Short but oh so sweet.  Just to the left of Water, start by traversing on a finger rail right then back left and up a thin seam. Move right just below the anchors
Short fun little route with the business up top. Cool movement on a vertical face to a rad sequence to gain the anchor.
content.protection: 5 bolts to a chain anchor with biners.
content.location: Right route on the far left of Jet A, just to the right of Curse of Mumm-Ra.

content.description: Climb up into the crack and under the steep blocky section.  Make a couple big moves through a sharp pocket and good hold to the forth bolt.  Now here is where the men/women are separated from the cheaters.  Go straight past the fifth bolt.  You could cut right and escape the difficulties, but know you will be a cheater!  Follow a left leaning ramp to the 6th bolt and into the real crux.  Fire straight up to another seam through some big moves and bad feet.  Finish in the crack to the right of the chains
content.location: Furthest route on the right.  Just to the left of a giant poo cave

content.description: A sharp route that climbs very well.  Starts with easier climbing then builds to more difficult moves as you trend right a bit, centering around one hard pull off crimp to a good pocket, compose yourself then head left to a sidepull then one more sharp crimp to a 'thankgod' rounded comfortable pocket.  Easier climbing to the top.
content.location: Starts just as the ground ramps up and left.  It is just to the right of Atomic Potato which has brown hangers.

content.description: Don't be deceived by the start; the challenge is at the top. The flake leads to pockets.
fun in-obvious climbing. Sustained climbing with a slab crux near the top.
content.location: Middle route on the far left of Jet A (Villainous Wall)

content.description: Start left of G.I Joe Bouncy Tanks. Head up easy ground to the right facing flake.  above the flake is the first crux, thin & sharp! after is more challenging climbing with an OK rest just before the final mind boggling crux.  Good Luck!

Fun little route on the Jet A wall. Great warm up! Description from the FA " there are NO BEES on this route. a truck spill set loose 20 million bees, whom proceeded to harass the fins indiscriminately for many daysÂ… luckily, there was enough reprieve to bolt this route"

Thanks for all the routes Tom!
content.protection: Bolts to biners at the anchor.
content.location: Just to the left of Atomic Potato. Furthest left route on the hill on the main section on Jet A.

content.description: A fun little route that keeps you thinking the whole way.
content.protection: 6-7 bolts to clips. Look for the Tan/Brown Hangers.
content.location: Just to the right of Bees? BEES!!!!!
